The paper deals with face recognition, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using unsupervised learning algorithms (Restricted Boltzmann Machines) to learn a shared representation, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Gabor features and PCA also suggests a focus on image processing (cs.MM). Finally, the evaluation of the method on different databases involves comparing and analyzing results, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR).
